      "description": "Royal Air Maroc (RAM) is set to resume its direct flights connecting Casablanca to Dubai (United Arab Emirates) and Doha (Qatar) starting in early July. A well-informed source within the company told Hespress that the decision was made after the security situation in the Middle East significantly improved. Once operations restart, the airline will offer […] The post Royal Air Maroc restores Dubai and Doha flights after Middle East tensions ease appeared first on HESPRESS English - Morocco News .",
